Here's a complete implementation:

```csharp
// In Program.cs

// Configure request size limit (before builder.Build())
builder.Services.Configure<FormOptions>(options =>
{
    options.MultipartBodyLengthLimit = 10 * 1024 * 1024; // 10 MB
});

// Also configure Kestrel if self-hosting
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(options =>
{
    options.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 10 * 1024 * 1024;
});

var app = builder.Build();

// Ensure uploads directory exists
var uploadsPath = Path.Combine(app.Environment.ContentRootPath, "uploads");
Directory.CreateDirectory(uploadsPath);

app.UseAntiforgery();

app.MapPost("/upload", async (IFormFile file) =>
{
    string[] allowedTypes = ["image/jpeg", "image/png"];
    string[] allowedExtensions = [".jpg", ".jpeg", ".png"];

    if (file.Length == 0)
        return Results.BadRequest("Empty file.");

    if (file.Length > 10 * 1024 * 1024)
        return Results.BadRequest("File exceeds 10 MB limit.");

    if (!allowedTypes.Contains(file.ContentType, StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase))
        return Results.BadRequest("Only JPEG and PNG files are allowed.");

    var ext = Path.GetExtension(file.FileName).ToLowerInvariant();
    if (!allowedExtensions.Contains(ext))
        return Results.BadRequest("Invalid file extension.");

    var fileName = $"{Guid.NewGuid()}{ext}";
    var filePath = Path.Combine(uploadsPath, fileName);

    await using var stream = new FileStream(filePath, FileMode.Create);
    await file.CopyToAsync(stream);

    return Results.Ok(new { fileName, size = file.Length });
})
.DisableAntiforgery(); // Remove this line if you want antiforgery enforced
.RequestSizeLimit(10 * 1024 * 1024);
```

**Key points:**

- **Size limits** are enforced at three levels: Kestrel, `FormOptions`, and the endpoint's `.RequestSizeLimit()` attribute.
- **MIME type + extension** are both validated to prevent spoofing.
- **`Guid` filenames** prevent path traversal and collisions.
- **`.DisableAntiforgery()`** — remove that chained call if your clients send the antiforgery token (browser forms). Keep it for API/mobile clients that won't have one.

If you want antiforgery enabled, remove `.DisableAntiforgery()` and ensure your form includes the token:

```html
<form action="/upload" method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data">
    @Html.AntiForgeryToken()
    <input type="file" name="file" />
    <button type="submit">Upload</button>
</form>
```
